{"name":"Stones taken from Thel-Emas’ Lost Temple","permission":{"default":0,"rJEU6XERAWNvCOnp":3},"type":"misc","data":{"description":"<p>Cast the stones on the ground. Their pattern reveals if danger lurks in an adjacent room. The stones can lie. The priest tests Presence DR10 to see if they are true but after failing they cannot test again until the sun has set.</p>","equipped":false,"price":0,"quantity":1},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/classitems/stones.png","effects":[],"_id":"Rgl8aSSYryuZisAf"}
{"name":"Fernor's Philtre","permission":{"default":0,"rJEU6XERAWNvCOnp":3},"type":"misc","data":{"description":"<p>Translucent oil, must be dabbed right into the eye. Heals infection and gives +2 on Presence tests for d4 hours.</p>","equipped":false,"price":0,"quantity":1},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/classitems/herbmasterdecoction.png","effects":[],"_id":"SBfkFuWHkoXbrzyc"}
{"name":"A Book of Boiling Blood","permission":{"default":0,"rJEU6XERAWNvCOnp":3},"type":"misc","data":{"description":"<p>You may open and read from this book once a day. Your enemy must make a DR12 test to prevent this. If they fail D2 Berserker-slayers (see page 60) appear from the depths of a forgotten dimension of blood. Roll a D6.</p>\n<p>On a 1&ndash;4 these creatures fight alongside you. On a 5&ndash;6 they turn on you, attempting to kill you and destroy the book. After the battle they return to their imprisonment.</p>","equipped":false,"price":0,"quantity":1},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/classitems/bookofboilingblood.png","effects":[],"_id":"X2ZRrHLgxAEfYlFz"}
{"name":"Bite Attack","permission":{"default":0,"rJEU6XERAWNvCOnp":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":"<p>DR10 to attack, d6 damage. You must be close to your target. 1&ndash;2 on d6 chance the enemy gets a free attack.</p>","equipped":false,"price":0,"quantity":1,"damageDie":"1d6","handed":"1","weaponType":"melee"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/classitems/biteattack.png","effects":[],"_id":"YyBop9YYBECckAlV"}
{"name":"Horn of the Schleswig Lords!","permission":{"default":0,"rJEU6XERAWNvCOnp":3},"type":"misc","data":{"description":"<p>Once per day release a blare from this dented old trumpet and test Presence DR12. One creature may make their next non-combat test an automatic success.</p>","equipped":false,"price":0,"quantity":1},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/classitems/trumpet.png","effects":[],"_id":"aEPj76uSqCM63ENj"}
{"name":"Crumpled Monster Mask","permission":{"default":0,"rJEU6XERAWNvCOnp":3},"type":"misc","data":{"description":"<p>Strikes primitive fear into lesser creatures like goblins, gnoums and children. While worn, they check Morale every round.</p>","equipped":false,"price":0,"quantity":1},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/classitems/crumpledmonstermask.png","effects":[],"_id":"cP0kvJBXKbYgwIo8"}
{"name":"Barbarister the Incredible Horse","permission":{"default":0,"rJEU6XERAWNvCOnp":3},"type":"container","data":{"description":"<p>Barbarister is magical, intelligent, arrogant and vain. He can also talk. If you can persuade him to care, Barbarister occasionally adds +2 to Presence tests</p>\n<p>involving logic and intellect. The horse may be smarter than you and is quite aware of this.</p>","equipped":false,"price":0,"quantity":1,"capacity":7},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/classitems/barbarister.png","effects":[],"_id":"cbcVHradQCKbeqT9"}
{"name":"Hamfund the Squire","permission":{"default":0,"rJEU6XERAWNvCOnp":3},"type":"misc","data":{"description":"<p>This intensely cowardly servant acts only as guardian for the scabbard of the cursed sword Eurekia. Once per combat, if Ham can be found, Eurekia may be drawn. The sword does 2d6 damage, and for every swing of Eurekia roll a d6. On a 1 the squire is slain and Eurekia vanishes forever.</p>","equipped":false,"price":0,"quantity":1},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/classitems/hamfund.png","effects":[],"_id":"dj4Vydf5ja2zUYZE"}
{"name":"Old Sigûrd’s sling","permission":{"default":0,"rJEU6XERAWNvCOnp":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":"<p>Sig&ucirc;rd was the strongest man whose throat you ever gnawed. Woven from his long grey hair, this sling has never failed you. 2d4 damage, requires fist-sized rocks which, perhaps regrettably, are everywhere.</p>","equipped":false,"price":0,"quantity":1,"damageDie":"2d4","handed":"1","weaponType":"ranged"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/items/weapons/sling.png","effects":[],"_id":"fPZXJYvl6nLSmswN"}
{"name":"Elixir Vitalis","permission":{"default":0,"rJEU6XERAWNvCOnp":3},"type":"misc","data":{"description":"<p>Heals d6 HP and stops infection. Can be habit-forming.</p>","equipped":false,"price":0,"quantity":1},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/classitems/herbmasterdecoction.png","effects":[],"_id":"hd1iYwjJScxIJWdz"}
{"name":"Poltroon the Court Jester","permission":{"default":0,"rJEU6XERAWNvCOnp":3},"type":"misc","data":{"description":"<p>While practically useless, personally irritating and an emotional drain, Poltroon&rsquo;s capering actually makes enemies lose their focus in combat. For the first two rounds you and your allies get +2 on attack/defence.</p>","equipped":false,"price":0,"quantity":1},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/classitems/jester.png","effects":[],"_id":"kj81Jlly8FdD2O3O"}
{"name":"Wizard Teeth","permission":{"default":0,"rJEU6XERAWNvCOnp":3},"type":"misc","data":{"description":"<p>Four weird teeth rattle within a blackened pouch. Before battle roll a d6 for each one. For every 6 one of your attacks deals maximum damage.</p>","equipped":false,"price":0,"quantity":1},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/classitems/wizardteeth.png","effects":[],"_id":"mbkV5GokdXxTjC4B"}
{"name":"Sacred shepherd’s crook","permission":{"default":0,"rJEU6XERAWNvCOnp":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":"<p>Its head a hook of human bone inscribed with overlapping anti-prayers. This crook hooks through other worlds. Staff does 2d4 damage except to faithless humans.</p>","equipped":false,"price":0,"quantity":1,"damageDie":"2d4","handed":"2","weaponType":"melee"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/classitems/shepherds-crook.png","effects":[],"_id":"mc3qwMG3gd9VPbb1"}
{"name":"The Snake-Skin Gift","permission":{"default":0,"rJEU6XERAWNvCOnp":3},"type":"misc","data":{"description":"<p>An expensive sandalwood box bound in snakeskin. It contains a seemingly ordinary dagger, wrapped in silk. The dagger does d4 damage but on a 1</p>\n<p>the target dies immediately of deadly poison weeping from the blade.</p>","equipped":false,"price":0,"quantity":1},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/classitems/snakeskingift.png","effects":[],"_id":"nCtTVJnb54rjpf5g"}
